<P>He complained of con&s;iderable nau&s;ea at his &s;tomach, but no vomiting. He &s;hortly after had a pa&s;&s;age, and void|ed a copious flow of urine.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="19" TYPE="experiment">
<HEAD>EXPERIMENT 19.</HEAD>
<P>To John Wheelder, a man of the &s;ame temperament, I gave four grains of the extract, deprived of its re&s;in. His pul&s;e beat 68 &s;trokes in a minute, and the following was the re&s;ult.</P>
